		<p><strong>Things I'm proud of </strong></p>
			<ul>
				<li>Randomiser function.</li>
				<li>An ‘Add to randomiser’ checkbox when setting up a category (not necessarily proud of the functionality of the checkbox, more how I got round the problem of not wanting to offer Drinks or Cakes).</li>
				<li>The dropdown box showing each category and then using this to filter results (category is an attribute of an item which belongs_to a retailer.</li>
			</ul>
    
    
    <p><strong>Future developments </strong></p>
			<ul>
				<li>Email with daily specials</li>
				<li>Login for visitors that would then allow them to save preferences</li>
				<li>Bulk update menus (rather than 1 item at a time)</li>
			</ul>
    

		<p><strong>Gems I used </strong></p>
			<ul>
				<li>Geocoder – To show the location of the theatre on a Google Map</li>
				<li>Paperclip – To upload an image for each </li>
				<li>Bootstrap and Bootstrap_form – For styling</li>
				<li>AWS-SDK – For storing the uploaded images</li>
				<li>Figaro – For authentication of the AWS account</li>
			</ul>
    

